{
  "number": 3760,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3760",
  "title": "rangeInput without Button",
  "body": "Since it's not possible to have a custom search field for a certain facet, I'd like to use rangeInput to have a similar functionality. But the rangeInput features a submit button which I would like to get rid of.\r\n\r\nSo the user would enter a value and instantly search / filter that facet. I could not find anything regarding that in the v3 docs.\r\n\r\nIs is possible to remove the button and use keyup instead? A better solution would be to have a second, single search field for a specific facet, but according to multiple SO entries, that is not possible.",
